Whenever you toggle a dropdown, remove the `active` class from all the other ones.&lt;br&gt;
Also it&#39;s better to add the `active` class to the dropdown container and then hide the content when that class is missing using css.&lt;br&gt;
Finally, I think it&#39;s more neat to manage each group separately (loop the dropdown containers and then add the event listener to the button that is inside them).

