In elasticsearch you can think of `&amp;&amp;` as `must` and `||` as should in [bool query][1], so you can translate this query

`(type == &quot;my-type&quot; || device_id == &quot;some-device-id&quot;) &amp;&amp; id == &quot;123456789&quot;`

as 

`must(should(type == &quot;my-type&quot;),(device_id == &quot;some-device-id&quot;), id == &quot;123456789&quot;`)

which gives us this query when we want to convert it to elasticsearch DSL

    {
      &quot;query&quot;: {
        &quot;bool&quot;: {
          &quot;must&quot;: [
            {
              &quot;bool&quot;: {
                &quot;should&quot;: [
                  {
                    &quot;term&quot;: {
                      &quot;type&quot;: {
                        &quot;value&quot;: &quot;my-type&quot;
                      }
                    }
                  },
                  {
                    &quot;term&quot;: {
                      &quot;device_id&quot;: {
                        &quot;value&quot;: &quot;some-device-id&quot;
                      }
                    }
                  }
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              &quot;term&quot;: {
                &quot;id&quot;: {
                  &quot;value&quot;: &quot;123456789&quot;
                }
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      }
    }

Hope that helps.

  [1]: https://www.elastic.co/blog/lost-in-translation-boolean-operations-and-filters-in-the-bool-query

